comment._content:
@Adam_Hodge, most of it was built for only temporary use - the white surface was actually plaster.

In this case at least, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World's_Columbian_Exposition">Wikipedia has it right</a>:
The White City, however, so impressed everyone who saw it ... that plans were considered to refinish the exteriors in marble or some other material. In any case, these plans were abandoned in July 1894 when much of the fair grounds was destroyed in a fire.
